<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>It’s important that the public, patients, ministers and staff have confidence that we’re making progress against our objectives and doing the things they expect of us.</p>

<p>The Department of Health and Social Care (<abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr>) boards and committees are responsible for making sure that we carry out our work as efficiently as possible, meeting our legal and other obligations. And they make sure that we’ve identified risks that might affect our work, and have plans in place to deal with these risks.</p>

<h2 id="dhsc-departmental-board">
<abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> departmental board</h2>

<p>The departmental board is the collective strategic and operational leadership of the department.</p>

<p>The board:</p>

<ul>
  <li>supports and advises ministers and the department on strategic issues linked to the development and implementation of the government’s objectives for the health and care system</li>
  <li>horizon scans for significant issues</li>
  <li>sets the overall strategic direction for the department in the light of ministerial priorities, the spending round settlement and the business plan</li>
  <li>ensures strategic alignment across the health and social care system</li>
  <li>oversees the management of risks within the department and its sponsored bodies</li>
  <li>oversees and monitors performance</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/departmental-board-annual-reports"><abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> departmental board annual reports</a></p>

<h3 id="departmental-board-meetings">Departmental board meetings</h3>

<p>The board meets once a quarter.</p>

<p>Departmental board meeting summaries from 2012 and earlier are available on the <a rel="external" href="http://transparency.dh.gov.uk/category/minutes-2/boards-committees/dh-board-meeting/">National Archives website</a></p>

<h3 id="departmental-board-members">Departmental board members</h3>

<p>Matt Hancock MP, Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, chairs the departmental board. Other members are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Caroline Dinenage MP, Minister of State for Care</li>
  <li>Chris Wormald, Permanent Secretary</li>
  <li>Professor Dame Sally Davies, Chief Medical Officer</li>
  <li>David Williams, Director General, Finance and Group Operations</li>
  <li>Lee McDonough, Director General, Acute Care and Workforce</li>
  <li>Jonathan Marron, Acting Director General, Community Care Group</li>
  <li>Clara Swinson, Director General, Global and Public Health Group</li>
  <li>Kate Lampard, Lead Non-Executive Director</li>
  <li>Gerry Murphy, Non-Executive Director & Chair of the Audit and Risk Committee</li>
  <li>Sue Bailey (non-executive)</li>
  <li>Mike Richards (non-executive)</li>
  <li>Michael Mire (non-executive)</li>
  <li>Ron Kerr (non-executive)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="dhsc-audit-and-risk-committee">
<abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> audit and risk committee</h2>

<p>The audit and risk committee advises the departmental board and the department’s accounting officer on risk management, corporate governance and assurance arrangements for <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> and its subsidiary bodies. It looks at:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the accounting policies, accounts and annual report of the Department, including reviewing them before their submission or audit</li>
  <li>issues arising from the annual report and accounts</li>
  <li>the annual governance statement</li>
  <li>the quality of risk management within the department, together with regular review of the strategic risk register</li>
  <li>the accountability arrangements established to support the accounting officer</li>
  <li>audit strategies and plans, and the department’s response to any issues identified by internal or external audits</li>
  <li>the department’s business code of conduct, anti-fraud policies, whistle-blowing policy and arrangements for special investigations</li>
  <li>how we respond to findings and recommendations from external bodies (for example, the House of Commons Public Accounts Committee)</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="audit-and-risk-committee-meetings">Audit and risk committee meetings</h3>

<p>The committee usually meets at least 4 times a year, with additional meetings in late spring and early summer to consider the annual report and accounts.</p>

<p>Read the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dh-audit-and-risk-committee-annual-reports"><abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> Audit and Risk committee annual reports</a></p>

<p>Audit and risk committee meeting summaries from 2012 and earlier are available on the <a rel="external" href="http://transparency.dh.gov.uk/category/minutes-2/arc-minutes/">National Archives website</a></p>

<h3 id="audit-and-risk-committee-members">Audit and risk committee members</h3>

<p>The current members are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Gerry Murphy (Chair)</li>
  <li>Jacqueline Burke</li>
  <li>Cat Little</li>
</ul>

<p>The committee decides which other civil servants should attend meetings. Chris Wormald and David Williams attend most meetings. They are usually joined by the <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> Head of Internal Audit and Mike Newbury, Director responsible for health at the National Audit Office.</p>

<h2 id="executive-committee">Executive committee</h2>

<p>The executive committee considers all major policy and operational issues that have a significant impact on the work of the Department of Health and Social Care. It supports the planning, co-ordination and delivery of ministerial priorities and supports the Permanent Secretary as Accounting Officer. The executive committee:</p>

<ul>
  <li>sets corporate governance and assurance arrangements for <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> and our subsidiary bodies (with advice from the audit and risk committee)</li>
  <li>considers and manage all strategic risks and issues that may have a significant impact on ministerial priorities and the wider health and care system advise ministers and the Departmental Board on the overall disposition and allocation of resources to <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> and the wider system</li>
  <li>oversees the structure and function of the department and the bodies it sponsors</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="executive-committee-meetings">Executive committee meetings</h3>

<p>The executive committee holds weekly meetings.</p>

<h3 id="executive-committee-members">Executive committee members</h3>

<p>Members of the executive committee are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Chris Wormald, Permanent Secretary</li>
  <li>Professor Dame Sally Davies DBE, Chief Medical Officer</li>
  <li>David Williams, Director General, Finance and Group Operations</li>
  <li>Lee McDonough, Director General, Acute Care and Workforce Group</li>
  <li>Jonathan Marron, Acting Director General, Community Care Group</li>
  <li>Clara Swinson, Director General, Global and Public Health Group</li>
  <li>Professor Chris Whitty, Chief Scientific Adviser</li>
</ul>

<p>Summaries to April 2012 are available on the <a rel="external" href="http://transparency.dh.gov.uk/category/minutes-2/boards-committees/dh-management-committee/">National Archives website</a></p>

<h3 id="management-committee">Management committee</h3>

<p>The Management Committee make decisions on matters relating to operations, finance, people, business planning, project delivery, assurance (in particular of ALBs), and transformational change.  In particular:</p>

<ul>
  <li>oversee the development of the business plan and ensure it is aligned with the Department’s strategic objectives</li>
  <li>maintains oversight of performance against the department’s financial and resource plans</li>
  <li>oversees the appropriate governance, assurance, structure and function of <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> and its sponsor bodies</li>
  <li>approves the governance statement and departmental performance narrative forming part of the <abbr title="Department of Health and Social Care">DHSC</abbr> annual report and accounts, and the annual report and governance statement</li>
  <li>is responsible for management of in-year changes to departmental budgets</li>
</ul>

<p>Members of the management committee are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>David Williams, Director General, Finance and Group Operations</li>
  <li>Kate Tilley, Director of <abbr title="Human Resources">HR</abbr>
</li>
  <li>Hugh Harris, Director of Strategy, System Oversight and Performance</li>
  <li>Paul Macnaught, Director of EU, International and Public Health System</li>
  <li>William Vineall, Director of Acute Care and Quality Policy</li>
  <li>Dr Louise Wood, Director of Science, Research and Evidence</li>
  <li>Elizabeth Woodeson, Director of Medicines and Pharmacy</li>
  <li>Chris Young, Finance Director</li>
  <li>Chris Mullin, Chief Economist, Director of Analysis</li>
</ul>

